The size is exactly as stated and planned for. Large would fit a 5'10" 180 person comfortably, neither baggy nor tight. The color is not the same light tan as shown in the advertisement photo, rather a darker shade with a hint of orange. The waistband edging inside the pants is not sewn the best. The material is average weight for occasional wear. Not satisfied overall so returning.

Absolutely love the fit and feel of these joggers. I wear them as daily casual wear pants and they are so great I ordered additional colors. Suggest washing on a cold water cycle, and only partially dry in clothes drier before hanging to fully air dry. This keeps them in great shape with no color fade or shrinking over time.

Bought a bunch of these colors. Here's my breakdown. Fit: I'm 5'9 180. I typically wear something like a 32x32. Bought these at Large..These fit really nice at the waist but I've found that the length was a bit long on all of these except A Khaki. Colors I would avoid because the pic doesn't quite match what you'll get. The darker grey is much darker than it looks. Light gray was much much nicer. And the darker blue looked like a weird blue to me. Almost like hospital scrubs. A Khaki and C Khaki are very similar and those pics are reliable. I also got black. If you want these to fit like a very skinny fit I'd go medium for sure. I bought large and found the length to be a bit too long and they have more of a relaxed baggy look. If you don't care about the skinny look then go for large if you're looking for something to just wear around the house. For some reason A Khaki was the absolute best perfect fit and how I wish all the rest fit.

I purchased these for myself. Im 6' tall and 300 lbs. Not a small guy. I struggle to get pants to fit me. Most of the time I need a belt to hold them up or the legs are too small in the thigh area. If your a big guy you know the problems. Let me just say these pants fit sooooo perfect I went and purchased 2 more pair. No need to use the drawstring they just stay up when sitting and or bending over. The stretch is awesome as well. Wish I had found these sooner.
